Let \(h\) = the height (in cm).  Then the base is \(b=4h+2\).  The area of the triangle is  
\[
\frac12\,b\,h \;=\;351
\;\Longrightarrow\;
\frac12(4h+2)\,h=351
\;\Longrightarrow\;
4h^2+2h=702
\;\Longrightarrow\;
2h^2+h-351=0.
\]

Use the quadratic formula on \(2h^2+h-351=0\):  
\[
h=\frac{-1\pm\sqrt{1+4\cdot2\cdot351}}{2\cdot2}
   =\frac{-1\pm\sqrt{2809}}{4}
   =\frac{-1\pm53}{4}.
\]
This gives \(h=13\) or \(h=-13.5\).  Discard the negative.  Hence
\[
\boxed{h=13\text{ cm},\quad b=4\cdot13+2=54\text{ cm}.}
\]
